thread.title: Faith Lutheran blanks Western, 45-0

title: Faith Lutheran blanks Western, 45-0
text:
The Sun's high school football section 
Faith Lutheran freshman Keegan Touchstone logged his third interception of the season today, returning it 75 yards for a touchdown in the Crusaders' 45-0 homecoming victory against Western . 
“It’s great to see a bright spot like that with guys stepping up,” Faith Lutheran coach Vernon Fox said. 
Brenden Joyce completed 13 of 22 passes for 266 yards and three touchdowns to lead Faith Lutheran, and Christian Marshall continued his great season with 11 carries for 96 yards and two touchdowns. 
Receiving touchdowns were by Elijah Kothe, Alec Netski and Brytton Weber. 
“We are sticklers for our expectation of being excellent each and every week,” Fox said. “There are certainly a number of things we could have done better.” Ray Brewer can be reached at 702-990-2662 or ray.brewer@lasvegassun.com . Follow Ray on Twitter at twitter.com/raybrewer21
